ParameterInfo.description: A list of CreateProjectInfo objects each of which define a TC_Project business object.

Operation.description: This operation creates TC_Project business objects using the given input. The newly created project will be active and visible with the current login user as Project Administrator and Project Team Administrator.
Operation.name: createProjects
Operation.returnDescription:
The newly created TC_Project business objects are returned in the ServiceData created objects list. If creation of one or more projects is not successful, partial errors are returned indicating why the project could not be created.

The following partial errors are returned:

* 101010: <projectId> ID already exists in the system. <projectId> ID must be unique within a site.
* 101002: The Project ID “<projectId>” is invalid.
* 101025: The entered Project name is either empty or contains blank spaces.
* 101026: The Project name <projectName> already exists. It must be unique within a site.
* 290013: Failed to check authorization.

ParameterInfo.description: Structure that holds the information required to get list of licenses.

Operation.description: This operation retrieves the Licenses attached to the given workspace objects . In case of multiple objects, only the licenses that are attached to all of the objects will be returned . It also retrieves level or structure information in case of ActiveWorkspace Content context. In ActiveWorkspace Content context, if the selected object do not have additional child objects then level or structure information are not be returned.
Operation.name: getLicensesWithTypes
Operation.returnDescription: The licenses attached to the given objects and the licenses that are available for attachment to those objects.

ParameterInfo.description: The TC_Project, filter, sort, expandNode, and pagination information specifying  the ProjectTeam information to return.

Operation.description: This operation returns the paginated output representing ProjectTeam for the given TC_Project object based on the input filter, sort and node information.
Operation.name: getProjectTeam
Operation.returnDescription:
The ProjectTeam members matching the input criteria with their status if applicable. Only user members have an associated status. The following partial errors may be returned:

•    101030:     The TC_Project is NULL or invalid.
•    101001:    The parentNode is invalid.
.
Operation.useCase:
The use cases below are examples of how the Project and filter information can be used to return specific ProjectTeam information. For any of the use cases, sort and pagenination can be added to input to determine the order and quantity of information returned from the service.

Return first level ProjectTeam:
Provide only the TC_Project object with no filter info to return the first level project team information. These are the project nodes that have explicitly been added to the ProjectTeam, for example Engineering group, or a specific Role within a Group such as Designer role.

Return specific user, group and members within the ProjectTeam:
Provide the TC_Project and filter information specifying a search string, if applicable, and the type(s) of member. The returned members may have been added explicitly to the Project Team or they may be included due to their group or role membership.

Return User members with one or more statuses within the TC_Project:
Provide the TC_Project and filter information including the status(es) of interest. The returned user members may have been added explicitly to the ProjectTeam or they may be included due to their Group or Role membership.

Return the members associated with a specific ProjectTeam node:
Provide the TC_Project, Group or Role , and filter . The returned User members may have been added explicitly to the ProjectTeam or they may be included due to their Group or Role membership.

ParameterInfo.description: Project Information which defines the properties to be set on new TC_Project business object.
Source project from which the project information should be copied.

Operation.description: This operation copies information from the given input TC_Project and creates a new project.
Operation.name: saveAsProject
Operation.returnDescription:
The newly created TC_Project business object is returned in the ServiceData created objects list. If creation of project is not successful, partial errors are returned indicating why the project could not be created.

The following partial errors are returned:

* 515106: There is already a project with the specified project ID
* 101002: The Project ID is invalid.
* 101025: The entered Project name is either empty or contains blank spaces.
* 101026: The Project name is already exists. It must be unique within a site.
* 101150: The Project name, "<projectName>", cannot be the same as the name of an existing Teamcenter Group.
* 101151: The Project ID, "<projectId>", already exists in the system. It must be unique within a site.
* 101152: The Project ID, "<projectId>", cannot contain the Teamcenter Program/Project differentiator '<differentiator>'.
* 101153: The Project Name, "<projectName>", cannot contain the Teamcenter Program/Project differentiator '<differentiator>'.
* 101154: The Project ID, "<projectId>", contains one or more invalid characters: '%', '*', '@'.
* 101155: The Project name, "<projectName>", contains one or more invalid characters: '.', '%', '*', '@'.
